mij last to you was on the 24 curtt, sence non from you att which I do
wonder, because you know I long fo Beare tow you proeud in the north in our
concennes, in the meane while I amglad to see 3 bales aboard of smish
whe is well arrived att ostend, the fine northres and bayes come in good
tune. now I exspect a good parcell or all the carsijes aboard Pindar which
I sipose I the nept & one or 2 bals of single doyns, ene bale of northrer
and one bale of fine northrens, with no less ther 1oo bayes, & thenthe rest
maij follon & the seeend ship. as for laces the last will be ready ny
weck to compleat yd ad, & ben iaclesed you gave an other leder to m. vande

Je should do itt, butt in case you save them all, you need not to give m the

I have before mee yd of 10 for by which you advise mee that a vessel is now
ready to sayle for Bruges, in deed my intention is & was to have att least
½ of my order aboard of that & according to yd promise shall exspect no less
& all if por, though I do confess that I do not much carn if the white
perpenancos should not come, provided, smight have the searges aboard of the
frrst a good nspasch, & ready mony is the liase of trade, & whe as I have
not much to say, because I supose you anow yd. owne Intrest, so will nott
large upon recommending more erinttley ny concerus, for in case you Incoriidge
mee, I shall incorridge you
